1
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:52,234
[JOHN]:
Hang on. I know.

2
00:00:52,235 --> 00:00:54,269
[KATE]:
Mm.

3
00:00:54,270 --> 00:00:56,605
You're doing so good.

4
00:00:56,606 --> 00:00:58,507
[JOHN]: You're doing so good.
You all right?

5
00:00:58,508 --> 00:01:00,309
- Yeah.
- Okay.

6
00:01:00,310 --> 00:01:03,312
<i>[WOMAN OVER PA]:
Dr. Matthews to the nurses' station.</i>

7
00:01:03,313 --> 00:01:05,047
[JOHN]:
Excuse me.

8
00:01:05,048 --> 00:01:09,251
My wife's in labor.
We called ahead for Dr. Wheeler.

9
00:01:09,252 --> 00:01:11,843
[MAN]:
I just need you to fill this out, please.

10
00:01:12,622 --> 00:01:15,349
- Thank you.
- Have a seat, hon.

11
00:01:17,627 --> 00:01:20,257
[GROANING]

12
00:01:22,065 --> 00:01:23,565
- I'll be right up.
- [KATE]: Yeah.

13
00:01:23,566 --> 00:01:27,158
- Okay?
- Okay.

14
00:01:27,637 --> 00:01:30,967
- Is this your first?
- No, no, it's our third.

15
00:01:30,974 --> 00:01:33,132
[MAN]:
Sir, can you sign here?

16
00:01:34,410 --> 00:01:38,002
We're gonna name her Jessica.

17
00:01:42,318 --> 00:01:45,186
[GROANING]

18
00:02:07,911 --> 00:02:10,138
[WOMAN]:
Vitals look good.

19
00:02:12,816 --> 00:02:14,449
[KATE]:
Where's John?

20
00:02:14,450 --> 00:02:17,085
- Where's my husband?
- [MAN]: Just relax now.

21
00:02:17,086 --> 00:02:19,119
Everything's gonna be okay.

22
00:02:25,228 --> 00:02:27,629
What's happening?
What are you doing?

23
00:02:27,630 --> 00:02:29,198
I'm so sorry for your loss.

24
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:31,466
- What?
- Your baby's dead.

25
00:02:31,467 --> 00:02:33,869
No, it's not dead. It's alive.

26
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:35,938
What are you talking about?
It's moving.

27
00:02:35,939 --> 00:02:39,274
It's a terrible loss. We're so sorry.

28
00:02:39,275 --> 00:02:42,878
- Just relax.
- No!

29
00:02:42,879 --> 00:02:45,914
What? No, no, no. Put me to sleep.
I wanna be asleep.

30
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:49,848
- [MAN]: It's too late for that.
- No!

31
00:02:52,956 --> 00:02:55,080
It's okay, you're doing great.

32
00:02:55,358 --> 00:02:57,492
What are you doing?
What are you doing?

33
00:02:57,493 --> 00:02:59,720
[MAN]:
You might feel some tugging.

34
00:03:02,131 --> 00:03:04,158
[SCREAMING]

35
00:03:05,168 --> 00:03:07,970
Oh, my God. This isn't happening.

36
00:03:07,971 --> 00:03:09,404
[BABY CRYING]

37
00:03:09,405 --> 00:03:13,075
Congratulations, Mrs. Coleman.
It's a girl.

38
00:03:13,076 --> 00:03:15,671
[SCREAMING]

39
00:04:28,551 --> 00:04:32,220
[WOMAN]: Yes, Kate, your dreams can be
a manifestation of your emotions.

40
00:04:32,221 --> 00:04:34,556
It's your body and mind's way
of dealing...

41
00:04:34,557 --> 00:04:37,225
with the stress and grief
of what happened.

42
00:04:37,226 --> 00:04:40,095
What if this has nothing to do
with the stillbirth?

43
00:04:40,096 --> 00:04:42,596
What do you think it's about?

44
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:46,769
We're seeing kids
for the first time this weekend.

45
00:04:46,770 --> 00:04:50,827
And maybe the nightmares...

46
00:04:53,977 --> 00:04:57,944
Maybe I'm just not ready to adopt yet.

47
00:05:03,186 --> 00:05:07,483
I drove by the wine shop
on the way home the other night.

48
00:05:08,391 --> 00:05:09,791
Did you stop?

49
00:05:09,792 --> 00:05:13,795
No. Wanted to. The thought
went through my brain, you know?

50
00:05:13,796 --> 00:05:15,897
It wasn't for myself. It wasn't...

51
00:05:15,898 --> 00:05:20,035
I just thought it would be nice to have
a bottle handy, in case we had guests.

52
00:05:20,036 --> 00:05:21,864
But you didn't go in.

53
00:05:23,906 --> 00:05:25,407
Mm-mm.

54
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:27,609
The key, to me...

55
00:05:27,610 --> 00:05:30,212
is not that you had the urge...

56
00:05:30,213 --> 00:05:32,047
but that you resisted it.

57
00:05:32,048 --> 00:05:36,118
You wouldn't have made it through
the home study if you weren't ready.

58
00:05:36,119 --> 00:05:37,753
But, ultimately...

59
00:05:37,754 --> 00:05:40,822
you have to decide.

60
00:06:03,546 --> 00:06:05,538
Hi.

61
00:06:06,182 --> 00:06:09,551
Honey, hello.

62
00:06:09,552 --> 00:06:12,254
Let me see. Ooh. Did you paint this?

63
00:06:12,255 --> 00:06:13,455
[SIGNING]

64
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:17,259
It's a beautiful butterfly.
It's fantastic.

65
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:19,561
Really wonderful. Good.

66
00:06:19,562 --> 00:06:23,154
Let's go. I'm cold.

67
00:06:40,349 --> 00:06:42,314
[CAR HORN HONKING]

68
00:06:44,087 --> 00:06:46,279
[TRUCK HORN HONKING]

69
00:06:51,327 --> 00:06:53,490
Are you okay?

70
00:07:49,852 --> 00:07:52,152
[THUDS]

71
00:07:55,658 --> 00:07:58,856
[HUMMING]

72
00:08:01,297 --> 00:08:03,858
[THUDDING]

73
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:14,066
Ah!

74
00:08:18,714 --> 00:08:20,116
Max!

75
00:08:20,117 --> 00:08:21,950
Max!

76
00:08:21,951 --> 00:08:23,818
Stop throwing!

77
00:08:23,819 --> 00:08:27,018
I'm working.

78
00:08:27,690 --> 00:08:29,124
KATE:
No, honey, I'm sorry.

79
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:31,826
Just take a break
for a little while, okay?

80
00:08:31,827 --> 00:08:35,487
Because Mommy's trying
to play. Okay?

81
00:08:39,202 --> 00:08:41,502
Daddy's here.

82
00:08:44,707 --> 00:08:46,740
- Mine.
- Hey.

83
00:08:47,210 --> 00:08:50,011
- Hi.
- Sorry, practice went a little late.

84
00:08:50,012 --> 00:08:53,080
- [KATE]: It's all right.
- [DANIEL]: Whoa.

85
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:56,817
- [JOHN]: Okay, tough guy. Give me that.
- [DANIEL]: Wicked.

86
00:08:57,587 --> 00:08:59,087
No, no.

87
00:08:59,088 --> 00:09:01,723
[JOHN]:
Shoot it, shoot it. Go, go, go, go.

88
00:09:01,724 --> 00:09:05,594
- [DANIEL]: No.
- [JOHN]: Yes! Give me five.

89
00:09:05,595 --> 00:09:07,729
Hey, how did it go? Daniel.

90
00:09:07,730 --> 00:09:09,688
Fine.

91
00:09:14,270 --> 00:09:16,570
JOHN:
Hey.

92
00:09:17,173 --> 00:09:18,373
Okay.

93
00:09:18,374 --> 00:09:20,442
DANIEL:
Five minutes. I'm at the last level.

94
00:09:20,443 --> 00:09:22,377
JOHN:
No more video games. Brush your teeth.

95
00:09:22,378 --> 00:09:25,247
[DANIEL]: That's no fair. It won't save.
Come on, Dad, please?

96
00:09:25,248 --> 00:09:26,748
[HEARING AID BEEPS]

97
00:09:26,749 --> 00:09:29,014
[MUTED SOUND]

98
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:50,364
[SIGNING]

99
00:10:37,587 --> 00:10:39,749
[SIGNING]

100
00:11:50,393 --> 00:11:51,993
[GASPS]

101
00:11:51,994 --> 00:11:53,195
Sorry.

102
00:11:53,196 --> 00:11:55,764
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

103
00:11:55,765 --> 00:11:57,359
God.

104
00:12:00,336 --> 00:12:02,337
[INHALES DEEPLY]

105
00:12:02,338 --> 00:12:04,235
You smell good.

106
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:17,442
Okay.

107
00:12:18,287 --> 00:12:20,713
All right.

108
00:12:23,926 --> 00:12:27,496
I have to stop being like this.

109
00:12:27,497 --> 00:12:29,791
JOHN:
I get it.

110
00:12:37,373 --> 00:12:41,709
I'm very excited, I'm happy.

111
00:12:41,710 --> 00:12:44,437
I get nervous.

112
00:12:44,713 --> 00:12:47,474
I'm really scared.

113
00:12:49,885 --> 00:12:55,057
Last time I felt all of this
was right before I lost the baby.

114
00:12:55,058 --> 00:12:58,760
I don't want you to feel like we have
to go through with this for my sake.

115
00:12:58,761 --> 00:13:02,263
It's not just- It's not for you.

116
00:13:02,264 --> 00:13:04,532
I wanna take the love
we felt for Jessica...

117
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:09,093
...and I wanna give it to somebody
who really needs it.

118
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:14,442
Are you sure, hon?

119
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:18,606
Yes.

120
00:13:39,502 --> 00:13:42,537
- [GIRL 1]: Wanna make a snowman?
- [GIRL 2]: Sure.

121
00:13:42,538 --> 00:13:44,537
[GIRL 3]:
It's really cold out here.

122
00:13:50,746 --> 00:13:52,547
[GIRL 4]:
Hey, stop it.

123
00:13:52,548 --> 00:13:54,342
[GIRL 5 GASPS]

124
00:13:59,788 --> 00:14:01,656
- [WOMAN]: Hi.
- [KATE]: Hi.

125
00:14:01,657 --> 00:14:03,124
So glad you could make it.

126
00:14:03,125 --> 00:14:05,818
- So are we.
- Yeah, finally, right?

127
00:14:06,161 --> 00:14:09,992
- So good to see you.
- [ABIGAIL]: Thank you for coming.

128
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:14,269
- This is really something.
- [ABIGAIL]: So go take a look around.

129
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:17,431
- Stay out of trouble.
- [JOHN]: Yeah, yeah.

130
00:14:20,242 --> 00:14:21,776
Look at the snow orphan.

131
00:14:21,777 --> 00:14:23,311
[KATE]:
Snow orphan?

132
00:14:23,312 --> 00:14:26,180
Uh, snorphan?

133
00:14:26,949 --> 00:14:29,346
[CHATTERING AND LAUGHING]

134
00:14:35,925 --> 00:14:40,791
- [GIRL]: Hey.
- [WOMAN]: No, show it to Sister Mary.

135
00:14:52,008 --> 00:14:56,441
[GIRL SINGING "GLORY OF LOVE"]

136
00:14:59,615 --> 00:15:02,308
[GIRLS LAUGHING]

137
00:15:02,952 --> 00:15:06,521
- [WOMAN]: Slow down, slow down.
- [GIRL 1]: You can't catch me.

138
00:15:06,522 --> 00:15:08,248
[GIRL 2]:
Yes, I can.

139
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:37,479
[ESTHER]:
Hello?

140
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:43,247
Hi.

141
00:15:43,726 --> 00:15:47,591
[ESTHER SINGING "GLORY OF LOVE"]

142
00:15:56,839 --> 00:15:58,840
Are all these paintings yours?

143
00:15:58,841 --> 00:16:03,172
- Yes. Do you like them?
- They're remarkable.

144
00:16:03,345 --> 00:16:04,912
Thank you.

145
00:16:04,913 --> 00:16:08,346
My name is Esther. What's yours?

146
00:16:08,350 --> 00:16:11,441
John. Nice to meet you.

147
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:15,381
- Can I take a seat?
- Of course.

148
00:16:16,692 --> 00:16:19,961
I never get tired of watching
these kids enjoy the party.

149
00:16:19,962 --> 00:16:22,664
It really is. I'm so sorry
we didn't do this sooner.

150
00:16:22,665 --> 00:16:24,666
Don't be. It's a big leap.

151
00:16:24,667 --> 00:16:29,397
Adopting an older child
is not an easy decision to make.

152
00:16:30,372 --> 00:16:31,706
KATE:
John's in the bathroom.

153
00:16:31,707 --> 00:16:34,242
[ABIGAIL]: Think he'll find us?
Do you wanna go look for him?

154
00:16:34,243 --> 00:16:39,247
- Where did you get the idea for this one?
- My paintings always tell stories.

155
00:16:39,248 --> 00:16:42,750
This one's about a sad mother lion
who can't find her cubs.

156
00:16:42,751 --> 00:16:46,688
- She's smiling.
- She's dreaming about her babies.

157
00:16:46,689 --> 00:16:48,791
It's the only thing
that makes her happy.

158
00:16:48,792 --> 00:16:53,794
- I hope she finds them.
- She will. Look.

159
00:16:56,398 --> 00:16:59,767
They were lost in the jungle,
and they were so scared...

160
00:16:59,768 --> 00:17:02,071
...because they didn't have a mother.

161
00:17:02,072 --> 00:17:04,639
Just when they thought
they'd be alone forever...

162
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:08,443
...they found their mother asleep
under this tree.

163
00:17:08,444 --> 00:17:12,113
Now when she wakes up,
her dream will have come true.

164
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:15,818
- She'll have her family again.
- Amazing. You came up with that story?

165
00:17:15,819 --> 00:17:18,909
- I think I hear his voice down here.
- Yes.

166
00:17:19,621 --> 00:17:23,292
Hey. I want to introduce you.
This is my wife, Kate.

167
00:17:23,293 --> 00:17:25,257
Kate, this is Esther.

168
00:17:26,095 --> 00:17:27,860
Hello.

169
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:32,898
How are you? Nice to meet you.

170
00:17:33,335 --> 00:17:35,770
She painted all these.

171
00:17:35,771 --> 00:17:36,972
- Really?
- Yeah.

172
00:17:36,973 --> 00:17:39,874
These are fantastic.
These are really wonderful.

173
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:42,443
- Thank you.
- Where did you learn how to do this?

174
00:17:42,444 --> 00:17:45,813
I've just had lots of time to practice,
I guess.

175
00:17:45,814 --> 00:17:48,783
It's really boring here.

176
00:17:48,784 --> 00:17:50,953
It's boring here?

177
00:17:50,954 --> 00:17:53,788
If you're so bored,
why aren't you down at the party?

178
00:17:53,789 --> 00:17:59,053
I've never really seen the point of it.
Nobody's ever talked to me before.

179
00:17:59,394 --> 00:18:00,661
I guess I'm different.

180
00:18:00,662 --> 00:18:03,030
There's nothing wrong
with being different.

181
00:18:03,031 --> 00:18:05,166
JOHN:
Well, you two have a lot in common.

182
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:07,660
[LAUGHING]

183
00:18:09,571 --> 00:18:11,673
ESTHER:
I think people should always...

184
00:18:11,674 --> 00:18:14,308
...try to take the bad things
that happen to them...

185
00:18:14,309 --> 00:18:16,844
...and turn them into something good.

186
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:19,814
- Don't you?
- Yeah.

187
00:18:19,815 --> 00:18:22,115
Absolutely.

188
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:32,060
She's originally from Russia, but it's
amazing how strong her English is.

189
00:18:32,061 --> 00:18:34,529
She's only been in the country
a few years.

190
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:36,731
You get children
from other countries?

191
00:18:36,732 --> 00:18:41,435
It's rare. But when we do,
it's sometimes difficult to place them.

192
00:18:41,436 --> 00:18:45,407
The family that brought her to America
died in a house fire.

193
00:18:45,408 --> 00:18:47,008
In a fire?

194
00:18:47,009 --> 00:18:48,576
My God.

195
00:18:48,577 --> 00:18:50,701
Esther barely got out.

196
00:18:50,879 --> 00:18:55,583
She's been through a lot, but this
is an extraordinary little girl.

197
00:18:55,584 --> 00:18:58,719
She's very bright.
She's very mature for her age.

198
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:03,024
And she's very well-mannered.
She's a bit of a princess, actually.

199
00:19:03,025 --> 00:19:07,425
She wears those ribbons on her wrists
and her neck all the time.

200
00:19:07,462 --> 00:19:08,696
Mine too.

201
00:19:08,697 --> 00:19:11,632
We had trouble with her
when we tried to take them off.

202
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:13,634
How does she get along
with other kids?

203
00:19:13,635 --> 00:19:16,070
Oh, when she has to interact,
she's great.

204
00:19:16,071 --> 00:19:18,372
Babe?

205
00:19:18,373 --> 00:19:21,742
- She really did seem to open up with us.
- Yeah.

206
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:24,712
[ABIGAIL]: I thought she more
than opened up with you.

207
00:19:24,713 --> 00:19:26,982
You seem to have made
quite a connection.

208
00:19:26,983 --> 00:19:31,746
I could get the paperwork together
and see you back here in three weeks.

209
00:19:37,459 --> 00:19:39,554
All right.

210
00:19:49,071 --> 00:19:50,304
Okey-dokey.

211
00:19:50,305 --> 00:19:52,506
[ABIGAIL]:
Call me if you need anything.

212
00:19:52,507 --> 00:19:54,871
Bye. Okay, thank you.

213
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:16,631
Oh, that's T~H.

214
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:19,433
T~H. Yeah.

215
00:20:19,434 --> 00:20:21,703
And " Max" is like this?

216
00:20:21,704 --> 00:20:23,361
[KATE]:
Yeah.

217
00:20:24,039 --> 00:20:26,031
Good.

218
00:20:29,978 --> 00:20:34,947
- Is this your house?
- [JOHN]: Now it's your house too.

219
00:20:50,799 --> 00:20:55,267
[KATE]: Hi, sweetie.
Hi. Look who's here.

220
00:20:59,708 --> 00:21:04,211
Hello, Max. My name is Esther.

221
00:21:04,212 --> 00:21:07,144
She's been practicing the whole way.

222
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:10,885
- Can she hear?
- [KATE]: A little.

223
00:21:10,886 --> 00:21:12,853
She was born almost completely deaf.

224
00:21:12,854 --> 00:21:16,652
That just allows her to hear enough
to read lips.

225
00:21:19,594 --> 00:21:22,263
[JOHN]:
That's all right, I got it.

226
00:21:22,264 --> 00:21:24,155
[DOOR OPENS]

227
00:21:26,501 --> 00:21:29,103
[JOHN]: I'd like to introduce you
to Grandma Barbara.

228
00:21:29,104 --> 00:21:31,973
It's a pleasure to meet you.

229
00:21:31,974 --> 00:21:35,566
That's precious.
It's a pleasure to meet you too.

230
00:21:36,712 --> 00:21:38,779
Danny.

231
00:21:38,780 --> 00:21:41,575
This is Esther.

232
00:21:43,085 --> 00:21:44,880
Hello, Daniel.

233
00:21:45,487 --> 00:21:47,616
Hey.

234
00:21:50,860 --> 00:21:52,893
[WHISPERS]
Why does she dress like that?

235
00:21:52,894 --> 00:21:56,230
- Come on. Stop it.
- I'm just asking a question.

236
00:21:56,231 --> 00:21:58,532
Oh!

237
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:02,069
- You have a piano?
- Yeah.

238
00:22:02,070 --> 00:22:05,798
- Would you like to learn how to play?
- I would love to.

239
00:22:14,449 --> 00:22:15,649
Do you like it?

240
00:22:15,650 --> 00:22:18,412
- It's perfect.
- [KATE]: Good.

241
00:22:25,328 --> 00:22:26,761
Thank you.

242
00:22:26,762 --> 00:22:29,130
How do you say "thank you"?

243
00:22:29,131 --> 00:22:30,831
Thank you.

244
00:22:30,832 --> 00:22:33,325
[SIGNING]

245
00:22:34,269 --> 00:22:37,201
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

246
00:22:40,075 --> 00:22:42,977
[JOHN]:
Wow, look at that.

247
00:22:42,978 --> 00:22:46,148
What? What? What?

248
00:22:46,149 --> 00:22:47,581
[DANIEL]:
Dad, look.

249
00:22:47,582 --> 00:22:49,283
