00:46:29,537 --> 00:46:32,738
Is there anything special
you want me to make tonight?

502
00:46:32,739 --> 00:46:34,407
You have any favorites?

503
00:46:34,408 --> 00:46:37,603
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

504
00:46:38,212 --> 00:46:39,679
Hello.

505
00:46:39,680 --> 00:46:43,217
- Well, how are you?
- Hi, we're great. We're doing good.

506
00:46:43,218 --> 00:46:45,218
<i>- How is she?
- [KATE]: She's here, hold on.</i>

507
00:46:45,219 --> 00:46:48,120
Hey, Sister Abigail.
Do you wanna say hello?

508
00:46:48,121 --> 00:46:52,714
- Come on. Esther, just quickly say hi.
- I said, no.

509
00:46:55,763 --> 00:47:01,493
You know what, do you mind, darling,
can you get five apples for me?

510
00:47:01,535 --> 00:47:04,404
Sorry, she got shy all of a sudden.

511
00:47:04,405 --> 00:47:07,006
It's all right.
I'm just calling to remind you...

512
00:47:07,007 --> 00:47:09,409
that I'm gonna need her medical...

513
00:47:09,410 --> 00:47:12,705
and dental charts
for my supervision report.

514
00:47:15,883 --> 00:47:18,418
She's not thrilled about the dentist.

515
00:47:22,389 --> 00:47:25,058
How is everyone doing?
Is she opening up to you?

516
00:47:25,059 --> 00:47:29,116
I guess you can say that. She dropped
the F-bomb on me a few weeks ago.

517
00:47:29,730 --> 00:47:31,565
[SIGNING]

518
00:47:31,566 --> 00:47:33,432
I guess she's finally
coming out of her shell.

519
00:47:33,433 --> 00:47:34,834
[LAUGHS]

520
00:47:34,835 --> 00:47:36,669
Yeah.

521
00:47:36,670 --> 00:47:38,605
Any other glitches I should know of?

522
00:47:38,606 --> 00:47:40,306
<i>We had a big one recently.</i>

523
00:47:40,307 --> 00:47:42,932
It's a girl named Brenda at school.

524
00:47:44,679 --> 00:47:48,247
They were at the playground,
there was a slide, well, she fell off.

525
00:47:48,248 --> 00:47:51,685
Esther may have pushed her down.

526
00:47:51,686 --> 00:47:54,453
I'm not getting the story straight,
but she got hurt.

527
00:47:54,454 --> 00:47:55,655
Is she all right?

528
00:47:55,656 --> 00:47:59,059
Luckily. She broke her ankle
and had something like 6 stitches.

529
00:47:59,060 --> 00:48:00,826
That doesn't sound too lucky.

530
00:48:00,827 --> 00:48:03,759
Well, she's lucky
she didn't break her neck.

531
00:48:08,268 --> 00:48:12,066
[PIANO PLAYING]

532
00:48:32,860 --> 00:48:35,728
You told me
you didn't know how to play.

533
00:48:35,729 --> 00:48:38,497
- No, I didn't.
- Yes, you did.

534
00:48:38,498 --> 00:48:41,601
You offered to teach me
and I accepted.

535
00:48:41,602 --> 00:48:47,174
Okay. So then you were
just pretending this whole time?

536
00:48:47,175 --> 00:48:49,308
I thought
you would enjoy teaching me.

537
00:48:49,309 --> 00:48:53,380
It must be frustrating for someone
who loves music as much as you...

538
00:48:53,381 --> 00:48:57,814
to have a son who isn't interested
and a daughter who can't even hear.

539
00:49:02,556 --> 00:49:05,249
Wait, wait, wait.

540
00:49:07,061 --> 00:49:09,862
I walk in on her playing Tchaikovsky
without a mistake.

541
00:49:09,863 --> 00:49:12,331
I mean, she's been lying to me
this whole time.

542
00:49:12,332 --> 00:49:15,369
[JOHN]: She just wants to spend time
with you. It's hardly a lie.

543
00:49:15,370 --> 00:49:16,569
[KATE]:
You wouldn't know.

544
00:49:16,570 --> 00:49:19,338
You wouldn't.
She's on her best behavior with you.

545
00:49:19,339 --> 00:49:22,575
She's completely different with me.

546
00:49:22,576 --> 00:49:24,510
So, what are you saying?

547
00:49:24,511 --> 00:49:27,047
I don't know.
She threw a fit at school.

548
00:49:27,048 --> 00:49:29,016
She pushed Brenda at the playground.

549
00:49:29,017 --> 00:49:33,085
- Now you're saying that was her fault?
- I don't know. Honey, I don't know.

550
00:49:33,086 --> 00:49:35,555
I wasn't there.
You were watching them.

551
00:49:35,556 --> 00:49:39,291
Oh, come on. It was an accident.

552
00:49:39,292 --> 00:49:42,696
Okay, let's not blame her
for anything, fine.

553
00:49:42,697 --> 00:49:44,530
I'll take her word for everything.

554
00:49:44,531 --> 00:49:47,801
Should I just believe what she said
about you and Joyce too?

555
00:49:47,802 --> 00:49:50,335
What did she say?

556
00:49:50,604 --> 00:49:54,675
- She says that you were hitting on her.
- What?

557
00:49:54,676 --> 00:49:58,444
Oh, come on. She must've
misunderstood. It was, like...

558
00:49:58,445 --> 00:49:59,945
Did she invite you over?

559
00:49:59,946 --> 00:50:03,283
She asked me
to help her move a chair.

560
00:50:03,284 --> 00:50:07,486
- She did?
- Yeah. I blew her off.

561
00:50:07,487 --> 00:50:10,057
Oh, God.

562
00:50:10,058 --> 00:50:11,424
Why didn't you tell me?

563
00:50:11,425 --> 00:50:13,426
- I...
- We could've laughed about it.

564
00:50:13,427 --> 00:50:15,395
- No, I knew how...
- You were hiding it.

565
00:50:15,396 --> 00:50:17,963
Honey, I knew how you'd react.

566
00:50:17,964 --> 00:50:20,332
Kate. Kate.

567
00:50:20,333 --> 00:50:23,336
You can't get jealous of every woman
that I talk to, right?

568
00:50:23,337 --> 00:50:25,838
- It's been like 10 years.
- What does that mean?

569
00:50:25,839 --> 00:50:28,207
You say that
like it actually means something.

570
00:50:28,208 --> 00:50:30,744
It's only been two years
since you told me.

571
00:50:30,745 --> 00:50:35,782
You know how sorry I am. I just feel
like I've earned a little trust here.

572
00:50:35,783 --> 00:50:39,652
- I gave you a second chance.
- That's not fair. That's not fair.

573
00:50:39,653 --> 00:50:43,023
Let me get this straight. We can talk
about my mistakes, not yours?

574
00:50:43,024 --> 00:50:46,726
I was sick! You were an asshole
who wanted to fuck somebody else!

575
00:50:46,727 --> 00:50:49,228
You put our child's life in danger.

576
00:50:49,229 --> 00:50:52,364
I could've walked away months ago.
Nobody would've blamed me.

577
00:50:52,365 --> 00:50:57,104
Oh, that's sharp. That's sharp. Where
did you get that from, your mother?

578
00:50:57,105 --> 00:51:00,138
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

579
00:51:10,551 --> 00:51:14,386
Danny. Turn that crap down,
please, I gotta work.

580
00:51:14,387 --> 00:51:16,045
- Fine.
- Thank you.

581
00:51:19,026 --> 00:51:20,326
[DOORBELL RINGS]

582
00:51:20,327 --> 00:51:22,622
[ESTHER]:
I'll get it.

583
00:51:27,534 --> 00:51:31,271
- Hello, Esther.
- What are you doing here?

584
00:51:31,272 --> 00:51:33,506
May I come in?

585
00:51:33,507 --> 00:51:37,042
I'm afraid I may have made a mistake.

586
00:51:37,043 --> 00:51:39,346
There could be something wrong
with Esther.

587
00:51:39,347 --> 00:51:40,713
What?

588
00:51:40,714 --> 00:51:43,983
What? You told us that you'd never
had any trouble with her.

589
00:51:43,984 --> 00:51:47,419
I didn't. But trouble
does have a way of finding her.

590
00:51:47,420 --> 00:51:49,078
What kind of trouble?

591
00:51:49,990 --> 00:51:52,359
Two girls get into a fight,
there she is.

592
00:51:52,360 --> 00:51:55,194
Someone gets caught stealing,
there she is again.

593
00:51:55,195 --> 00:51:57,563
- So? Does that mean-?
- Just let her finish.

594
00:51:57,564 --> 00:52:02,001
After you told me about the girl in
the playground, I called her old school.

595
00:52:02,002 --> 00:52:04,603
While she was there,
there was a boy...

596
00:52:04,604 --> 00:52:06,740
who fell with scissors in his hand...

597
00:52:06,741 --> 00:52:09,542
and accidentally stabbed himself
through the jaw.

598
00:52:09,543 --> 00:52:11,210
And Esther was there again.

599
00:52:11,211 --> 00:52:15,178
I don't understand.
He accidentally stabbed himself.

600
00:52:15,215 --> 00:52:18,350
But the most troubling thing
is the Sullivan house fire.

601
00:52:18,351 --> 00:52:21,977
I checked into it further.
It was arson.

602
00:52:22,422 --> 00:52:24,957
They have never found the person
who did it.

603
00:52:24,958 --> 00:52:27,127
JOHN:
What are you suggesting here?

604
00:52:27,128 --> 00:52:29,628
That she had anything to do
with any of this?

605
00:52:29,629 --> 00:52:31,096
It's ridiculous.

606
00:52:31,097 --> 00:52:33,266
[ABIGAIL]:
That a child could commit such crimes...

607
00:52:33,267 --> 00:52:35,334
it flies in the face
of everything I believe.

608
00:52:35,335 --> 00:52:37,168
Well, yeah.

609
00:52:39,874 --> 00:52:41,875
[DOOR OPENS]

610
00:52:41,876 --> 00:52:46,446
There's a mean lady here.
She's come to take me away.

611
00:52:46,447 --> 00:52:48,582
Will you help me?

612
00:52:48,583 --> 00:52:52,384
We've had
some behavioral problems, but...

613
00:52:52,385 --> 00:52:55,222
Yeah, nothing like that.
I mean, right?

614
00:52:55,223 --> 00:52:58,090
- Yes, we have.
- [JOHN]: Really, hon, think about it.

615
00:52:58,091 --> 00:53:01,962
I've tried to reach the Russian
orphanage where she was raised.

616
00:53:01,963 --> 00:53:04,730
I think we need to know
what we're dealing with.

617
00:53:04,731 --> 00:53:07,400
Well, I'll tell you
what we're dealing with.

618
00:53:07,401 --> 00:53:09,635
- [KATE]: No, you know what?
- Stop it. Listen.

619
00:53:09,636 --> 00:53:12,972
We're dealing with a 9-year-old girl
who's an orphan, okay?

620
00:53:12,973 --> 00:53:17,600
- We're taking her to Dr. Browning.
- We can take her to Dr. Browning.

621
00:53:21,082 --> 00:53:23,813
[SIGNING]

622
00:54:14,434 --> 00:54:16,627
[SPEAKING]
Do you want to play?

623
00:54:23,311 --> 00:54:26,145
[ABIGAIL]: I'll call you
as soon as I find anything else out.

624
00:54:26,146 --> 00:54:28,881
- [JOHN]: Right. Take care.
- [KATE]: Okay. Thank you very much.

625
00:54:28,882 --> 00:54:30,944
Maybe later.

626
00:54:51,505 --> 00:54:52,705
It's going to be fine.

627
00:54:52,706 --> 00:54:56,639
We'll scare her so bad
she'll never come back here.

628
00:55:04,352 --> 00:55:05,552
Here she comes.

629
00:55:05,553 --> 00:55:07,753
Wave your arms and make her stop.

630
00:55:07,754 --> 00:55:09,382
Max, go.

631
00:55:18,699 --> 00:55:20,690
[YELLS]

632
00:55:27,874 --> 00:55:31,038
[GROANING]

633
00:55:38,619 --> 00:55:41,520
You all right? Max?

634
00:55:41,521 --> 00:55:43,650
Max?

635
00:55:43,823 --> 00:55:45,282
You okay?

636
00:55:47,261 --> 00:55:50,185
[SCREAMING]

637
00:55:58,338 --> 00:56:00,540
Stop crying.

638
00:56:00,541 --> 00:56:05,177
Grab a foot
and help me get her off the road.

639
00:56:05,178 --> 00:56:07,171
Now.

640
00:56:53,527 --> 00:56:56,754
[ABIGAIL GRUNTING]

641
00:57:15,749 --> 00:57:19,749
Help me hide her.

642
00:57:55,923 --> 00:57:57,457
[SIGNING]

643
00:57:57,458 --> 00:57:59,158
That doesn't matter.

644
00:57:59,159 --> 00:58:02,896
They'll send you to jail
just for helping me hide her.

645
00:58:02,897 --> 00:58:07,330
I had to kill her because
she was going to tell on me.

646
00:58:08,268 --> 00:58:13,828
You're not going to tell on me.
Are you?

647
00:58:22,615 --> 00:58:24,083
Don't worry.

648
00:58:24,084 --> 00:58:26,418
You're my little sister.

649
00:58:26,419 --> 00:58:29,721
I won't let anything
happen to you.

650
00:58:29,722 --> 00:58:31,613
I love you.

651
00:59:41,761 --> 00:59:44,162
Tell me what you saw.

652
00:59:44,163 --> 00:59:47,133
- What are you doing?
- What did you see?

653
00:59:47,134 --> 00:59:49,468
I saw you and Max
in the tree house.

654
00:59:49,469 --> 00:59:51,036
What else?

655
00:59:51,037 --> 00:59:53,539
- What do you mean?
- What else did you see?

656
00:59:53,540 --> 00:59:55,374
I didn't see anything. I swear.

657
00:59:55,375 --> 00:59:57,909
- Did you tell anyone?
- No.

658
00:59:58,144 --> 01:00:00,076
I didn't tell anyone.

659
01:00:01,148 --> 01:00:02,481
Please...

660
01:00:02,482 --> 01:00:06,719
If I find out that you're lying,
I'll cut your hairless little prick off...

661
01:00:06,720 --> 01:00:10,117
before you even figure out
what it's for.

662
01:00:10,556 --> 01:00:14,092
- Do you understand me?
- Yes.

663
01:00:16,896 --> 01:00:19,123
You pissed yourself.

664
01:00:30,275 --> 01:00:32,910
It was nice talking to you, Alice.
I hope we can be friends.

665
01:00:32,911 --> 01:00:35,537
I'd like that.

666
01:00:35,849 --> 01:00:39,315
- We'll be right out, honey.
- You can come on in.

667
01:00:46,358 --> 01:00:49,561
My initial instinct is that...

668
01:00:49,562 --> 01:00:53,961
there's not a deeply-rooted problem
in Esther's past.

669
01:00:54,067 --> 01:00:58,693
- So there's nothing wrong with her?
- No.

670
01:01:01,274 --> 01:01:04,342
It's not all good news.
I think what needs to be examined...

671
01:01:04,343 --> 01:01:07,969
is Esther's relationship
with those around her.

672
01:01:08,370 --> 01:01:09,608
Specifically with you, Kate.

673
01:01:09,609 --> 01:01:13,578
It seems she feels there's been some
real tension between the two of you.

674
01:01:13,579 --> 01:01:16,915
- Okay.
- She's doing her best to please you...

675
01:01:16,916 --> 01:01:19,949
but you're blocking her attempts
to bond.

676
01:01:20,854 --> 01:01:25,324
That's not true. That's not true
at all, I've done everything.

677
01:01:25,325 --> 01:01:28,194
- Right?
- Just let her finish.

678
01:01:28,195 --> 01:01:31,264
Something's happening
to cause Esther to feel this way.

679
01:01:31,265 --> 01:01:35,803
Perhaps it's your guilt about
drinking or what happened to Max.

680
01:01:35,804 --> 01:01:38,672
Maybe some of your feelings
of inadequacy as a mother...

681
01:01:38,673 --> 01:01:42,176
are manifesting themselves
in your relationship with Esther.

682
01:01:42,177 --> 01:01:44,939
I don't feel inadequate.

683
01:01:47,682 --> 01:01:49,584
What did she tell you?

684
01:01:49,585 --> 01:01:53,278
She didn't see. She doesn't know.

685
01:01:53,889 --> 01:01:56,124
She's so stupid.

686
01:01:56,125 --> 01:01:59,962
Esther's a very shy, reserved...

687
01:01:59,963 --> 01:02:04,192
sensitive little girl going through
an extremely difficult time.

688
01:02:04,401 --> 01:02:07,031
[GRUNTING]

689
01:02:10,307 --> 01:02:14,400
She's exceptionally bright
and highly articulate.

690
01:02:16,882 --> 01:02:20,848
She just needs a little patience
and understanding.

691
01:02:24,925 --> 01:02:26,790
[SCREAMS]

692
01:02:38,271 --> 01:02:40,964
Thanks for your support back there.

693
01:02:41,273 --> 01:02:44,105
That was your idea.

694
01:02:45,246 --> 01:02:46,880
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

695
01:02:46,881 --> 01:02:49,015
Kate, wait, wait, wait.

696
01:02:49,016 --> 01:02:52,519
I'm not a psychiatrist,
but a lot of what she said made sense.

697
01:02:52,520 --> 01:02:55,020
Do you wanna get that?

698
01:02:58,594 --> 01:03:00,927
<i>- Hello?
- Hello, is this Mrs. Coleman?</i>

699
01:03:00,928 --> 01:03:02,196
Yes. Who's this?

700
01:03:02,197 --> 01:03:04,298
This is Sister Judith
from St. Mariana's.

701
01:03:04,299 --> 01:03:06,668
I'm sorry to bother you,
but I need to know...

702
01:03:06,669 --> 01:03:09,705
if Sister Abigail
made it to her appointment with you.

703
01:03:09,706 --> 01:03:12,040
Yes. Why?

704
01:03:12,041 --> 01:03:14,076
<i>She hasn't returned since yesterday...</i>

705
01:03:14,077 --> 01:03:17,771
<i>and I'm just starting
to get really worried.</i>

706
01:03:27,726 --> 01:03:30,725
[MAN]: Charlie 24,
you wanna hold them there?

707
01:03:35,333 --> 01:03:37,324
Hey.

708
01:03:43,008 --> 01:03:45,543
[MAN]:
Okay, I think we're done.

709
01:03:46,479 --> 01:03:50,115
[KATE]: Detective, do you have
any leads or suspects?

710
01:03:50,116 --> 01:03:54,120
- [MAN]: No, not yet.
- I just don't understand...

711
01:03:54,121 --> 01:03:56,821
this kind of thing.
Who would do this? It's...

712
01:03:56,822 --> 01:03:58,024
Awful.

713
01:03:58,025 --> 01:04:00,494
You think of anything else,
you give us a call.

714
01:04:00,495 --> 01:04:02,585
[KATE]:
Yes. Absolutely.

715
01:04:02,862 --> 01:04:04,855
Let's go.

716
01:05:01,027 --> 01:05:04,363
This is what Sister Abigail
was talking about. Look.

717
01:05:04,364 --> 01:05:08,233
"Character-disturbed children".
Look at the symptoms.

718
01:05:08,234 --> 01:05:13,932
"Superficially charming. Difficulty
at making and keeping friends".

719
01:05:14,074 --> 01:05:16,010
I'm not sure this is what she meant.

720
01:05:16,011 --> 01:05:20,546
She could've told Dr. Browning
whatever she wanted to hear. Look.

721
01:05:22,550 --> 01:05:24,818
They "are adroit manipulators...

722
01:05:24,819 --> 01:05:28,822
oftentimes playing people off
one another to get what they want".

723
01:05:28,823 --> 01:05:31,225
Well, you gonna show this
to Dr. Browning?

724
01:05:31,226 --> 01:05:34,094
I'm not showing her anything.

725
01:05:34,095 --> 01:05:35,930
I'm not seeing her anymore.

726
01:05:35,931 --> 01:05:39,067
- When did you decide that?
- When do you think?

727
01:05:39,068 --> 01:05:41,102
You're gonna discount Dr. Browning?

728
01:05:41,103 --> 01:05:45,504
Why does everyone get the benefit
of the doubt from you except for me?

729
01:05:54,851 --> 01:05:58,088
If you need help with the kids,
we can arrange that.

730
01:05:58,089 --> 01:06:00,953
I don't need help.

731
01:06:09,368 --> 01:06:11,369
I just wanna know more about her.

732
01:06:11,370 --> 01:06:15,474
I wanna know where she came from,
and I wanna know who she is.

733
01:06:15,475 --> 01:06:17,876
What if Sister Abigail was right?

734
01:06:17,877 --> 01:06:20,813
I mean, if someone was in danger,
our own children...

735
01:06:20,814 --> 01:06:23,682
- wouldn't you wanna know?
- Of course I would.

736
01:06:23,683 --> 01:06:27,619
I'll contact the orphanage she came
from in Russia. All right?

737
01:06:27,620 --> 01:06:29,744
I mean, it's a start.

738
01:06:30,090 --> 01:06:32,221
[CLATTERING]

739
01:06:39,533 --> 01:06:42,761
- What?
- [JOHN]: Hey.

740
01:06:48,611 --> 01:06:50,277
Fine.

741
01:06:50,278 --> 01:06:53,782
I was wondering if you'd heard from
anyone at the Sludyanka Shelter.

742
01:06:53,783 --> 01:06:57,018
Sister Abigail had mentioned
that she would...

743
01:06:57,019 --> 01:06:58,613
Oh, you did.

744
01:07:01,358 --> 01:07:05,155
I don't understand. How can they
have no record of her being there?

745
01:07:06,330 --> 01:07:07,797
Yes, please.

746
01:07:07,798 --> 01:07:12,528
Could you just call me as soon as
you know anything, please? Thank you.

747
01:07:43,904 --> 01:07:46,096
[JOHN]:
Esther, we gotta go.

748
01:07:52,179 --> 01:07:54,275
Esther?

749
01:07:57,884 --> 01:08:00,015
Esther?

750
01:08:01,055 --> 01:08:02,557
You got me.

751
01:08:02,558 --> 01:08:04,482
[JOHN LAUGHS]

752
01:08:05,294 --> 01:08:08,262
- What?
- I don't want to go to the dentist.

753
01:08:08,263 --> 01:08:11,065
- Why not?
- I just don't want to go.

754
01:08:11,066 --> 01:08:13,896
- What, are you scared?
- No.

755
01:08:15,206 --> 01:08:17,238
We're gonna reschedule, though.

756
01:08:17,239 --> 01:08:21,644
Tell you what, I'll let you play hooky
if you want to come and draw with me.

757
01:08:21,645 --> 01:08:23,979
All right.

758
01:08:27,251 --> 01:08:29,119
[KATE]:
Wait, Daniel.

759
01:08:29,120 --> 01:08:33,177
How are you two getting along
with Esther?

760
01:08:35,093 --> 01:08:36,427
Fine, I guess.

761
01:08:36,428 --> 01:08:38,359
- [KATE]: Yeah?
- [DANIEL]: Yeah, Mom.

762
01:08:40,064 --> 01:08:44,269
But has she ever made you feel,
I don't know, uncomfortable...

763
01:08:44,270 --> 01:08:47,862
or has she done anything
that she's not supposed to do?

764
01:08:48,274 --> 01:08:53,004
- No.
- Like, has she ever hurt any of you?

765
01:08:53,546 --> 01:08:55,739
[DANIEL]:
No.

766
01:08:58,685 --> 01:09:00,484
You sure?

767
01:09:03,558 --> 01:09:07,251
Okay. All right.

768
01:09:08,262 --> 01:09:11,064
[ESTHE]: I like it
when it's just the two of us.

769
01:09:11,065 --> 01:09:15,303
You don't know how long I've waited
for a daddy just like you.

770
01:09:15,304 --> 01:09:17,371
Mommy too, right?

771
01:09:18,773 --> 01:09:20,808
I don't think
Mommy likes me very much.

772
01:09:20,809 --> 01:09:22,377
Hey.

773
01:09:22,378 --> 01:09:25,113
- That is not true. Mommy loves you.
- It's all right.

774
01:09:25,114 --> 01:09:28,384
It must be hard to love an
adopted child as much as your own.

775
01:09:28,385 --> 01:09:33,444
Sweetheart, you're just as much a part
of this family as Danny and Max. Okay?

776
01:09:33,957 --> 01:09:37,360
Do something nice for Mommy.
Show her how much you love her.

777
01:09:37,361 --> 01:09:40,485
That's a wonderful idea.

778
01:09:59,519 --> 01:10:02,279
I have a special surprise
for you, Mommy.

779
01:10:02,654 --> 01:10:04,454
You do?

780
01:10:05,692 --> 01:10:09,022
I picked these flowers
just for you.

781
01:10:11,397 --> 01:10:17,536
- Esther, what did you do? God.
- [ESTHER]: My arm!

782
01:10:17,537 --> 01:10:19,072
- [KATE]: Why did you do this?
- Daddy, my arm!

783
01:10:19,073 --> 01:10:20,641
[ESTHER SCREAMS]

784
01:10:20,642 --> 01:10:21,941
- [KATE]: John!
- Hey.

785
01:10:21,942 --> 01:10:25,145
- [KATE]: What did you do?
- [JOHN]: Hey. Stop, stop.

786
01:10:25,146 --> 01:10:26,380
Why did you do this?

787
01:10:26,381 --> 01:10:29,650
- Oh, God. God, she did this on purpose.
- No, no, no.

788
01:10:29,651 --> 01:10:31,251
- Yes, she did.
- Hey. Honey, no.

789
01:10:31,252 --> 01:10:33,854
She knew
what these roses meant to me.

790
01:10:33,855 --> 01:10:37,358
It's my fault, hon. I told her
to do something nice for you.

791
01:10:37,359 --> 01:10:39,655
I can't believe this.

792
01:11:59,849 --> 01:12:02,513
[GROANING]

793
01:12:10,795 --> 01:12:13,555
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

794
01:12:21,271 --> 01:12:24,136
[ESTHER]:
Daddy!

795
01:12:24,275 --> 01:12:26,939
Daddy!

796
01:12:27,680 --> 01:12:30,349
Daddy, Daddy!

797
01:12:30,350 --> 01:12:32,006
What is it, honey?

798
01:12:32,050 --> 01:12:34,811
My arm still hurts.

799
01:12:39,158 --> 01:12:42,795
Can I have a look at it?
You're okay.

800
01:12:42,796 --> 01:12:45,396
I'll be gentle.
It's all right, honey.

801
01:12:45,397 --> 01:12:47,561
Oh, my God.

802
01:12:49,035 --> 01:12:52,127
We need to take you
to the hospital.

803
01:12:56,110 --> 01:12:58,713
[JOHN]: You're a brave little girl,
you know that?

804
01:12:58,714 --> 01:13:02,111
Doctor said
you're gonna heal real fast, okay?

805
01:13:18,034 --> 01:13:19,829
You broke her arm.

806
01:13:23,339 --> 01:13:25,642
[KATE]: It's impossible.
I didn't grab her that hard.

807
01:13:25,643 --> 01:13:31,340
She wants to sleep in here tonight.
Maybe you should sleep downstairs.

808
01:13:50,669 --> 01:13:53,704
I'm having guests for dinner.

809
01:13:57,244 --> 01:14:00,540
You know,
you can have it. Thanks.

810
01:15:03,348 --> 01:15:06,178
[KATE]:
Have a good day.

811
01:15:13,494 --> 01:15:15,260
Daniel.

812
01:15:15,261 --> 01:15:17,389
Your books.

813
01:15:20,500 --> 01:15:24,366
- What happened? Let me see your bag.
- I don't know.

814
01:15:26,040 --> 01:15:30,134
We just bought this.
Pick it up, it's gonna get wet.

815
01:15:36,118 --> 01:15:38,178
Mom!

816
01:15:39,988 --> 01:15:43,820
[KATE]:
Max! No! Help!

817
01:15:44,726 --> 01:15:46,695
Max!

818
01:15:46,696 --> 01:15:48,296
[KATE SCREAMING]

819
01:15:48,297 --> 01:15:50,255
Max!

820
01:15:56,573 --> 01:15:59,198
[CAR HORN HONKING]

821
01:16:02,213 --> 01:16:04,171
Max!

822
01:16:11,289 --> 01:16:13,323
Max!

823
01:16:13,324 --> 01:16:15,259
Are you okay?

824
01:16:15,260 --> 01:16:18,796
I'm here. Mommy's here.
You're okay, honey. Come on.

825
01:16:18,797 --> 01:16:24,358
I got you. Yeah. Oh, baby,
it's okay. I'm so sorry.

826
01:16:25,804 --> 01:16:28,474
I remember I put it in park
and I set the brake.

827
01:16:28,475 --> 01:16:31,344
Max didn't indicate
that Esther did anything.

828
01:16:31,345 --> 01:16:36,615
Well, Max is covering for her.
And I don't think it's the first time.

829
01:16:36,616 --> 01:16:40,744
It also wouldn't be the first time
you blamed Esther for your own mistake.

830
01:16:43,691 --> 01:16:46,326
You know what?
I want her out of this house.

831
01:16:46,327 --> 01:16:48,762
You're ready for somebody
to come and take her?

832
01:16:48,763 --> 01:16:51,366
I am. I don't care.

833
01:16:51,367 --> 01:16:55,368
I will do whatever it takes
to protect my children.

834
01:16:55,369 --> 01:16:57,666
The girls found this this morning.

835
01:16:58,007 --> 01:17:00,875
The girls found it.
You mean Esther found it.

836
01:17:00,876 --> 01:17:03,678
Yes, Esther. Does it make
any difference? Is she lying?

837
01:17:03,679 --> 01:17:04,980
[BROWNING]:
You need help.

838
01:17:04,981 --> 01:17:08,183
We've reserved a place for you
in a rehabilitation facility...

839
01:17:08,184 --> 01:17:10,686
about 45 minutes from here.

840
01:17:10,687 --> 01:17:12,220
[KATE]:
I didn't drink it.

841
01:17:12,221 --> 01:17:15,824
I bought two bottles.
I poured one of them down the sink.

842
01:17:15,825 --> 01:17:17,727
- But not this one?
- No.

843
01:17:17,728 --> 01:17:21,697
John, I haven't had a drink
in almost a year.

844
01:17:21,698 --> 01:17:24,334
We wanna help you,
but there's nothing we can do...

845
01:17:24,335 --> 01:17:28,604
- until you stop lying to yourself.
- I'm not lying. I wanted to drink it.

846
01:17:28,605 --> 01:17:32,342
You have no fucking idea how badly
I wanted to drink it, but I didn't.

847
01:17:32,343 --> 01:17:34,878
- I didn't drink it.
- If Max had gotten hurt...

848
01:17:34,879 --> 01:17:38,650
What happened this morning
has nothing to do with this.

849
01:17:38,651 --> 01:17:40,843
I find that hard to believe.

850
01:17:41,020 --> 01:17:45,785
The only reason that I'm sober
is because of Max and Daniel.

851
01:17:46,259 --> 01:17:49,995
I think about what would have
happened had you not been there...

852
01:17:49,996 --> 01:17:52,198
and it makes me wanna kill myself.

853
01:17:52,199 --> 01:17:54,133
I would never do anything...

854
01:17:54,134 --> 01:17:57,369
to let something like that
ever happen again. I wouldn't.

855
01:17:57,370 --> 01:17:59,840
That is so manipulative.

856
01:17:59,841 --> 01:18:03,375
I know I haven't given you reason
to believe me, I know I haven't.

857
01:18:03,376 --> 01:18:05,879
I lied to you.
I should have told you about this.

858
01:18:05,880 --> 01:18:09,383
I'll go to therapy, I'll go to fucking
A.A. if that's what you want...

859
01:18:09,384 --> 01:18:11,918
- but you have to believe me.
- I don't.

860
01:18:11,919 --> 01:18:14,923
You have to believe me.
John, you have to trust me on this.

861
01:18:14,924 --> 01:18:17,525
I'll give you a week
to go to rehab...

862
01:18:17,526 --> 01:18:20,228
or I'm leaving
and I'm taking the kids with me.

863
01:18:20,229 --> 01:18:22,597
I think that's fair, okay?

864
01:18:22,598 --> 01:18:25,300
I'll help you as much as I can,
make it really easy.

865
01:18:25,301 --> 01:18:27,269
Mom's gonna come in the afternoon.

866
01:18:27,270 --> 01:18:32,408
All right? I'm willing to do this.
I'm willing to try and figure this out.

867
01:18:32,409 --> 01:18:36,808
- But it's up to you.
- I'll shoot Mommy if you tell.

868
01:18:37,448 --> 01:18:41,018
[ESTHER HUMMING]

869
01:18:57,136 --> 01:19:00,432
Max. Max, are you okay?

870
01:19:01,008 --> 01:19:05,099
What did she do? Did she do something
to make the car crash?

871
01:19:06,212 --> 01:19:11,083
If you saw her, you have to help me,
so Mom and Dad can protect us.

872
01:19:11,084 --> 01:19:12,974
[SIGNING]

873
01:19:13,620 --> 01:19:15,214
Why not?

874
01:19:23,999 --> 01:19:26,691
Is that Sister Abigail?

875
01:19:33,242 --> 01:19:36,744
Max. What did she do
in my tree house?

876
01:19:38,982 --> 01:19:41,276
Are the bad things still there?

877
01:19:44,020 --> 01:19:46,155
Everything's gonna be okay.

878
01:19:46,156 --> 01:19:51,490
I'll get the stuff from the tree house.
Then they'll have to believe us.

879
01:20:38,046 --> 01:20:41,448
- Going somewhere, Kate?
- What are you doing here?

880
01:20:41,449 --> 01:20:44,119
She's fine. Let's not wake her.

881
01:20:44,120 --> 01:20:45,453
Go to your room.

882
01:20:45,454 --> 01:20:49,190
Honestly, we're past that now.
Aren't we?

883
01:20:49,191 --> 01:20:51,850
I know what you're doing.

884
01:20:52,429 --> 01:20:54,461
I will not let you
hurt my children.

885
01:20:54,462 --> 01:20:55,865
Me?

886
01:20:55,866 --> 01:20:59,634
I'm not the one who passed out drunk
and let Max almost drown in the pond.

887
01:20:59,635 --> 01:21:01,237
If it wasn't for John...

888
01:21:01,238 --> 01:21:05,638
she'd be dead,
and you'd probably still be in jail.

889
01:21:06,978 --> 01:21:08,669
Who told you that?

890
01:21:10,781 --> 01:21:12,576
It's very intimate.

891
01:21:12,917 --> 01:21:14,751
- I learned so much.
- Give it to me.

892
01:21:14,752 --> 01:21:18,456
- Jessica. Your cheating husband.
- Esther, give it to me.

893
01:21:18,457 --> 01:21:20,425
Where you hide your wine bottles.

894
01:21:20,426 --> 01:21:22,927
I'm... I'm warning you
right now.

895
01:21:22,928 --> 01:21:25,430
"She was still kicking
when the doctor told me...

896
01:21:25,431 --> 01:21:28,300
it was something called phantom...

897
01:21:28,301 --> 01:21:29,934
fetal movement.

898
01:21:29,935 --> 01:21:33,773
- For 16 days, I carried my dead baby".
- Stop it. Esther.

899
01:21:33,774 --> 01:21:37,176
" It was the cruelest torture
I could imagine".

900
01:21:37,177 --> 01:21:39,779
Stop it. You stop it.

901
01:21:39,780 --> 01:21:42,080
What's wrong with you?

902
01:21:42,081 --> 01:21:45,018
Kate, it's too late.
It's your own fault.

903
01:21:45,019 --> 01:21:47,280
You took your family for granted.

904
01:21:47,288 --> 01:21:51,017
- What do you mean?
- What are you going to do?

905
01:21:52,093 --> 01:21:54,189
Hit me?

906
01:21:59,534 --> 01:22:02,770
We adopted her from you.
How could you not know anything?

907
01:22:02,771 --> 01:22:05,206
The Sullivans
could have adopted her illegally.

908
01:22:05,207 --> 01:22:08,777
<i>She doesn't remember anything
that could help us?</i>

909
01:22:10,045 --> 01:22:12,136
I'm gonna call you back.

910
01:23:28,999 --> 01:23:32,465
"Saarne Institute".

911
01:23:44,216 --> 01:23:47,409
[LINE RINGING]

912
01:23:47,818 --> 01:23:50,955
[WOMAN SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE OVER PHONE]

913
01:23:50,956 --> 01:23:54,926
Hello. Do you speak English?

914
01:23:54,927 --> 01:23:56,627
[WOMAN SPEAKS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

915
01:23:56,628 --> 01:23:58,463
Do you speak English?

916
01:23:58,464 --> 01:24:00,632
Is there anyone
who speaks English there?

917
01:24:00,633 --> 01:24:02,767
This is very important.

918
01:24:02,768 --> 01:24:06,031
[SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

919
01:24:06,672 --> 01:24:08,637
I don't know what you're saying.

920
01:24:21,354 --> 01:24:23,856
- Hello?
- Is this the Saarne Institute?

921
01:24:23,857 --> 01:24:25,591
<i>Yes.</i>

922
01:24:25,592 --> 01:24:29,195
Yes. I need to talk to somebody
about one of your children.

923
01:24:29,196 --> 01:24:31,998
She was adopted by an American family.
It's a girl.

924
01:24:31,999 --> 01:24:35,301
<i>She is not come from here.</i>

925
01:24:35,302 --> 01:24:37,604
Well, I haven't even
told you her name yet.

926
01:24:37,605 --> 01:24:40,641
You do not understand.
Saarne Institute is not an orphanage.

927
01:24:40,642 --> 01:24:42,607
It is a mental hospital.

928
01:25:10,041 --> 01:25:12,610
Are you looking for this?

929
01:25:14,211 --> 01:25:16,211
Poor Sister Abigail.

930
01:25:16,814 --> 01:25:21,753
I couldn't have done it myself,
you know. Max is just as guilty as I am.

931
01:25:21,754 --> 01:25:25,623
- Whatever Max did, you made her do it.
- Think about it.

932
01:25:25,624 --> 01:25:28,716
How did she even know
what was up here?

933
01:25:28,727 --> 01:25:32,065
It's always better
to burn the evidence.

934
01:25:32,066 --> 01:25:37,134
If they find these things,
they won't just be coming for me.

935
01:25:37,135 --> 01:25:39,466
They'll be coming for Max too.

936
01:25:40,341 --> 01:25:42,839
- Is that really what you want?
- Wait.

937
01:25:44,044 --> 01:25:45,975
What're you doing?

938
01:25:46,580 --> 01:25:48,773
Are you crazy?

939
01:25:54,857 --> 01:25:56,356
Let me out!

940
01:25:56,357 --> 01:25:58,789
Let me out of here!

941
01:26:08,538 --> 01:26:11,930
Mom!

942
01:26:12,042 --> 01:26:17,246
It's called the Saarne Institute.
S~A~A~R~N~E, Saarne.

943
01:26:17,247 --> 01:26:18,680
<i>It's in Estonia.</i>

944
01:26:18,681 --> 01:26:23,420
Estonia? No, this can't be right.
All of her paperwork is from Russia.

945
01:26:23,421 --> 01:26:25,988
I'm sending them a picture
of her right now.

946
01:26:25,989 --> 01:26:28,925
Maybe her birth mother
was a patient there.

947
01:26:28,926 --> 01:26:32,086
I don't know.
Maybe she was even born there.

948
01:26:36,835 --> 01:26:39,294
Mom!

949
01:26:39,705 --> 01:26:42,973
Help!

950
01:26:48,248 --> 01:26:51,339
[SCREAMING AND GRUNTING]

951
01:26:58,724 --> 01:27:01,355
Mom! Dad!

952
01:27:08,335 --> 01:27:10,038
Oh, God!

953
01:27:10,039 --> 01:27:12,929
[SCREAMS]

954
01:27:19,114 --> 01:27:21,876
Oh, God. Call 911!

955
01:27:33,163 --> 01:27:36,288
Don't worry.
You're going to heaven.

956
01:27:38,403 --> 01:27:40,764
[KATE]:
Oh, God!

957
01:27:42,507 --> 01:27:47,566
Oh, my God! Daniel!

958
01:27:47,578 --> 01:27:50,180
Move away! Move away from the fire!

959
01:27:50,181 --> 01:27:51,415
Daniel?

960
01:27:51,416 --> 01:27:55,887
Oh, God, no. Daniel?
Mommy's right here. Can you hear me?

961
01:27:55,888 --> 01:27:59,058
Please wake up.
Honey, Mommy's right here, okay?

962
01:27:59,059 --> 01:28:01,888
You're gonna be all right.

963
01:28:11,672 --> 01:28:16,108
We stopped the abdominal bleeding,
but he has a very serious neck injury.

964
01:28:16,109 --> 01:28:20,348
He's stabilized for now. You should
consider yourselves very lucky.

965
01:28:20,349 --> 01:28:22,883
- Can we see him?
- [DOCTOR]: In a little while.

966
01:28:22,884 --> 01:28:25,018
He's resting in the ICU.

967
01:28:25,019 --> 01:28:28,623
Okay. And will he be able
to tell us what happened?

968
01:28:28,624 --> 01:28:30,357
[DOCTOR]:
It's possible.

969
01:28:30,358 --> 01:28:34,053
No way of knowing for sure what
he'll remember until he wakes up.

970
01:28:34,230 --> 01:28:36,220
Excuse me.

971
01:28:38,601 --> 01:28:41,032
It's gonna be okay.

972
01:28:44,207 --> 01:28:48,478
JOHN: I know you're exhausted
and upset, and so am I.

973
01:28:48,479 --> 01:28:52,447
There has to be some other explanation.
She didn't come from an insane asylum.

974
01:28:52,448 --> 01:28:56,953
The orphanage you thought
she came from has never heard of her.

975
01:28:56,954 --> 01:28:58,888
Everything about her could be a lie.

976
01:28:58,889 --> 01:29:02,057
We have her passport. We have
school records, medical records.

977
01:29:02,058 --> 01:29:04,361
These are papers
from around the world.

978
01:29:04,362 --> 01:29:06,564
What is this?
It's a piece of paper.

979
01:29:06,565 --> 01:29:11,397
Your own mother was there this time. It
wasn't just me. Your mother was there.

980
01:29:11,436 --> 01:29:14,506
It's either Esther
or Daniel who started the fire.

981
01:29:14,507 --> 01:29:17,442
- Who do you think it was?
